cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning model based on LSTM for predicting hourly concentrations of fine dust in Seoul. This involves time series analysis and capturing non-linear interactions between multiple variables. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, which deal with artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper also involves the use of climate variables, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.IR (information retrieval) or cs.SI (social and information networks). Finally, the use of LSTM suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing).
